           <div class="theoryprophecy">
                <div class="theorytext"> <p><strong> A self-fulfilling prophecy</strong> occurs when the expectations that appearance creates are realized. Chubby cheeks, a big forehead, or a soft jawline may lead to social interactions that elicit “babyish” or playful behavior. The behavior can then have an influence on the individual, creating a self-fulfilling prophecy. <span class="theorytextemphasis">People may acquire the psychological traits that their facial appearance led others to expect.</span></p>
                </div>

