           <div class="theoryprophecy">
                <div class="theorytext"> <p> <strong>A self-defeating prophecy</strong> effect occurs when the expectations that appearance creates produce effects that elicit behavior just the opposite of what is expected. <span class="theorytextemphasis"> Often, the target of the personality expectancies defeats them  </span> because the social interactions produced by the expectancies are negative. For example, the chubby-cheeked boy who is expected to be innocent may reject this childlike image and compensate by rebelling.</p>
